Remarks.

Trichonothrus hallidayi

can be differentiated from the only other member of the genus, 

T. austroafricanus

Mahunka, 
1986


, based on the following combination of characters: 
1
) the large, stout, heavily barbed lamellar setae; 
2
) the strongly inflated lateral prodorsal region; 
3
) the stout, heavily barbed exobothridial setae; 
4
) with notogastral seta 
