2
displaced posteriomedially; 
5
) with a complete circumdorsal scissure; 
6
) with four pairs of setae on the centrodorsal region enclosed by the circumdorsal scissure; 
7
) notogaster oval; posterior margin rounded; 
8
) epimeral setae long, flagellate apically and barbed basally; 
9
) epimeral setal formula 

